## Metric Naming Convention
{{- if .HasProfile}}
Pattern: **`{{.Profile.Observability.MetricNaming}}`**

Rules:
- All segments lowercase, dot-separated
- `service` = the name of this service (from `forge.project_id` in config.yaml)
- `operation` = the specific action (e.g. `charge`, `login`, `fetch_user`)
- `result` = `success`, `failure`, or `error`

Examples:
- `{{.ProjectID}}.charge.success`
- `{{.ProjectID}}.charge.failure`
- `{{.ProjectID}}.db_query.duration` (use `.duration` suffix for timers)
{{- else}}
<!-- Define metric naming pattern, e.g. service.operation.result -->
{{- end}}

## Structured Logging

Every log line must include these fields:

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `service` | string | Service name (matches `forge.project_id`) |
| `trace_id` | string | Propagated from request context |
| `span_id` | string | Current span ID |
| `level` | string | `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error` |
| `msg` | string | Human-readable message |
| `error` | string | Error message (on error logs only) |

**Never log PII** (emails, names, phone numbers, payment details). Never log secrets or tokens.

## Required Instrumentation

Every service must instrument:

- [ ] **Request duration** — histogram, tagged by endpoint and status code
- [ ] **Error rate** — counter, tagged by error type
- [ ] **Dependency health** — DB connection pool stats, cache hit/miss ratio, external API latency
- [ ] **Business events** — domain-specific metrics (e.g. `payments.charge.success`)
- [ ] **Startup / shutdown** — log service start with version and config (redacted)

## SLOs
{{- if .HasProfile}}
{{- if .Profile.Observability.SLOEnabled}}
SLO definitions are **required** for all user-facing endpoints. Define in ARCHITECTURE.md:

- Availability target (e.g. 99.9%)
- Latency target (e.g. p95 < 200ms)
- Error budget policy (e.g. alert at 10% burn rate over 1h)
{{- else}}
SLOs are not required for this profile. Define informally in ARCHITECTURE.md if applicable.
{{- end}}
{{- else}}
